I understand how poisonous it can be to breed resentment, but that's exactly why i'm bothered. I'm learning to let myself succeed mid-grief for my old, much more hopeful, sense of the world around me so that i can more effectively better us toward how i wish things already were.

Bugs me how even my greatest personal successes in navigating life with a fucky brain reflect a just-out-of-reach timeline where I wouldnt have had to suffer and develop the will to continue if only the average person wasn't so ignorant, cruel, emotionally immature, insensitive.
